# AI Bubble Oracle — environment variables (all optional; comments only, no values)
#
# The project reads plain environment variables (there is no dotenv loader —
# export these in your shell, or set them as GitHub Actions secrets).
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#   Enables the Claude Haiku layers: buzz-spike news classification and the
#   cached Then & Now per-metric observations. Absent => deterministic
#   fallbacks; the build never blocks on it.
#
# ORACLE_ENABLE
#   Comma-separated metric keys to activate beyond each module's
#   enabled_by_default — this is how you turn on a committed credential-gated
#   module in your own clone (e.g. ORACLE_ENABLE=example_metric).
#   Never set this in .github/workflows/daily-update.yml: the public site is
#   public-data-only, and `python main.py check` enforces that.
#
# ORACLE_DISABLE
#   Comma-separated metric keys to force off (renders as a tree stub).
#
# Credential-gated sources declare their own variables in SOURCE["requires"],
# e.g. a Bloomberg module might require:
#   BLOOMBERG_API_HOST
#   BLOOMBERG_API_TOKEN
# A module is skipped (stub) until every variable it requires is set.
